\pard\f0\fs28 Leaves alternate, or the involucral ones subopposite; sheaths adnate to the leaf-base, ligulate, or free from the leaf-base and stipuliform. Carpels (1-)4, free or shortly connate at the base. Fruitlets drupaceous, with bony endocarp and softer exocarp; embryo unciform or spiral.
